replies.bodyText:
That's true. Having this forces the extension developers to have a 1-arg constructor for its extension-specific configuration class (like this), if they wish to have its configuration.
Otherwise, I think what we can do is to support both 0-arg and 1-arg constructors like this?
try {
  extraConfig = project.getObjects().newInstance(extraConfigType.get());
} catch (SomeExceptionFromNotBeingAbleToInstantiate ex) {
  extraConfig = project.getObjects().newInstance(extraConfigType.get(), project);
}
